<div type="translation" source="bib:Gillet2024_01">

<p>Fortune! Prosperity! This is the 5th year of Kōpparakesarivarman. To Mahādeva of Tiruvālantuṟai of Ciṟupaḻuvūr, a <foreign>brahmadeya</foreign> in Kuṉṟakkūṟṟam, the chieftain <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>araiyaṉ</foreign></supplied> of Perumpuliyūr Maṇaṟkuṭi in Poykaināṭu, Tēvaṉ Nāṭṭi, to burn <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>eriya</foreign></supplied> a lamp <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>viḷakku</foreign></supplied>, for one handful <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>oru piṭiya</foreign></supplied> of <foreign>ghee</foreign> <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>neyyikku</foreign></supplied>, gave <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kuṭutta</foreign></supplied> in the care of <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>vacam</foreign></supplied> those of the Sabhā <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>sabhaiyār</foreign></supplied> of this Ciṟupaḻuvūr 22 undying and non-ageing <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>cāvāmūvā</foreign></supplied> great goats <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>perāṭu</foreign></supplied>. This is under the protection of the Panmāheśvaras (<foreign>panmaheśvara</foreign> &gt; <foreign>panmāheśvara</foreign>).</p></div>

